text:
Hey <@U02PNAGUP0W> I don't think there is something like that. That seems like it would be a duplication of the endpoint.

Below is a sample response for a deal I made. You can see for example that this deal has 3 tasks. I don't have to retrieve their ID's separately. If you need all notes, emails, and tasks you can just make an array with ID's of the activities.
But if you're referring to the part where you have to fetch data for those ID's after you got them, for that I think you'll have to make separate calls. You can use engagements API from the docs, but I haven't seen any batch option for this.

